He was charged as part of Operation Yewtree, the police investigation prompted by the Jimmy Savile abuse scandal, but the accusations against Travis have no connection to the disgraced television presenter.

He is charged with one offence of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged 18, in 1977; two offences of indecent assault relating to a girl, aged 15, in 1977; one offence of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged 19, in 1978; one offence of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged between 26 and 28, on a date between 1981 and 1983; one offence of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged 18, in 1983; one offence of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged between 19 and 20,on a date in 1985; one offence of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged 22, in 1990; three offences of indecent assault relating to a woman, aged between 26 and 29, from 2000 to 2003 and one offence of sexual assault relating to a woman, aged 23, in 2007.

